    <text>
        <body>
            <div frus:doc-dateTime-max="1934-07-18T11:00:00-05:00"
                frus:doc-dateTime-min="1934-07-18T11:00:00-05:00" n="288"
                subtype="historical-document" type="document" xml:id="d288">
                <note rend="inline" type="source">611.1431/52: Telegram</note>
                <head>
                    <hi rend="italic">The Minister in Guatemala</hi> (<persName type="from">
                        <hi rend="italic">Hanna</hi>
                    </persName>) <hi rend="italic">to the <gloss type="to">Secretary of
                            State</gloss>
                    </hi>
                </head>
                <opener>
                    <dateline rendition="#right">
                        <placeName>
                            <hi rend="smallcaps">Guatemala</hi>
                        </placeName>, <date calendar="gregorian" when="1934-07-18T10:00:00-06:00"
                            >July 18, 1934—10 a.m.</date>
                        <lb/>[Received 12:15 p.m.]</dateline>
                </opener>
                <p>47. Department’s 24, July 17, 8 p.m., concerning trade agreement with Government
                    of Guatemala. I judge from recent conversations with the Minister of Foreign
                    Affairs of Guatemala that it would now be agreeable to this Government to begin
                    exploratory conversations for a reciprocal trade agreement.</p>
                <closer>
                    <signed>
                        <hi rend="smallcaps">Hanna</hi>
                    </signed>
                </closer>
            </div>
        </body>
